als and count how many Roman characters are required to write it.\n\n16. Retrieve the page about the 2005 Texas ballot proposition on family law and state the calendar date when the vote occurred.\n\n17. How many language links appear at the top of the encyclopedic essay that surveys the conservative political doctrine emphasizing traditional family roles and social morals?\n\n18. Once again, look up Uruguay’s population figure and record the same headcount you used earlier.\n\n19. What is Uruguay’s total land area, expressed in square kilometres?\n\n20. Take that area value and determine its largest prime factor.\n\n21. How many temples are located near the coordinates 37°20′32″N 121°55′07″W (37.342172, -121.918542)?\n\n22. Again retrieve Uruguay’s population total and note it precisely as reported.\n\n23. Calculate the number of days between 2005-11-08 and 2026-03-16; what is that day-count?\n\n24. Reverse the digits of the day-count you just calculated — what number do you get when its digits are written backwards?\n\n25. Finally, compute the digital root of (clue 1 + clue 22) and give the result; the correct answer will be a single digit between 0 and 9.",
